A woman who reportedly lied she was pregnant today appeared before a Milimani court.   Elizabeth Musembi was arrested after she was found with a pillow strapped to her belly to make it look like she was pregnant.  Musembi appeared before Senior Principal Magistrate Bernard Ochoi under miscellaneous application.  The police asked court to give them five more days to detain and take Musembi to Mathari Mental Hospital for assessment before charging her.  The case will be mentioned on Wednesday.  DNA test to be conducted on stolen baby  Kuresoi woman fakes pregnancy, buys a baby to cover her tracks  Lifeline for two rugby players jailed for rape  Court holds proceedings outside as country fights coronavirus  Ajuza mmoja alazimika kulala katika kituo cha polisi kwa madai ya kutolipa kodi  Moses Kuria fails to take plea at Milimani law court following assault charges  Moses kuria asomewa mashtaka kortini kwa kumshambulia mwanamke katika kituo cha Royal Media By Julius Chepkwony | 4 hours ago By Collins Kweyu | 10 hours ago By Collins Kweyu | 10 hours ago By James Wanzala | 10 hours ago